[[Continue->The End 3]]Jed and the others left the empty store, grabbing their belongings and valuables. They began the trek out of town, going around the port and along the river. There was an aura of melancholy and sorrow around the group. No one wanted to speak. Everyone was lost in their own thoughts, perhaps reliving the memories of their soon-to-be-former home. Jed thought about his time in Webster Groves. How he started as just an average guy who took the opportunity to help when he could, to stopping an alien invasion, to becoming mayor, to helping keep Webster Groves as safe as possible during the zombie invasion. It was unfortunate that not everyone could be saved, and that now the town itself could not be saved, but this was out of Jed's hands. At the very least, he had to tell himself that for the betterment of his mental health. It was the next morning after everyone left that Webster Groves blew up, completely destroying everything. All that was left was a gigantic crater where the town used to be, with no signs of life or infrastructure anywhere. They had no idea where they would go, but one thing was certain: they could never come back.
